  "prompt": "What is Amazon MTurks?",
  "response": "Amazon Mechanical Turk (MTurk) is an online crowdsourcing marketplace owned and operated by Amazon. It allows businesses, researchers, and individuals (known as \"requesters\") to outsource small tasks, called Human Intelligence Tasks (HITs), to a large, distributed workforce (called \"workers\" or \"Turkers\").\n\nKey features of MTurk include:\n\n1. Task types: Tasks range from data verification, image/video processing, surveys, transcription, content moderation, to simple data entry.\n\n2. Flexible work: Workers can complete tasks from anywhere, at any time, using their computer or mobile device.\n\n3. Small payments: Tasks typically pay very small amounts, often just a few cents per task.\n\n4. Global workforce: Workers come from various countries, though the majority are from the United States and India.\n\n5. Requesters can customize tasks and set their own payment rates.\n\n6. Payment is made through Amazon Payments or Amazon.com gift cards.\n\nThe platform gets its name from an 18th-century mechanical chess-playing \"turk\" that appeared to play chess autonomously, but was actually operated by a human hidden inside.\n\nMTurk is commonly used in academic research, data collection, machine learning training, and by businesses needing large-scale, low-cost human-powered task completion.",
